Full details on the 55 Countries and 11 partially recognized Countries/Territories that allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry or Visa on arrival. Have you ever suffered Visa refusal at one time or the other, in various embassies in Lagos and Abuja for flimsy reasons? Then this article on “Nigeria Passport Visa Free Countries In Europe Or Other Parts Of The World” would be perfect for you.
Perhaps, you’ve experienced frustrations in meeting their draconian visa requirements, and you’re about to give up your desire or plan to spend your next holiday outside the country. Do not give up because we’re here to illustrates a list of 52 Countries and 11 partially recognised Countries/territories where Nigerians can travel to without Visa.


Nigeria Passport Visa Free Countries In Europe Or Other Part Of The World
 
1. ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA – Capital – St. John’s, an Island country located in the West Indies allows Nigerian citizens Electronic entry visa.
2. BARBADOS – Capital Bridgetown Saint Michael, an Island country located in the Caribbean in the continent of North America, allows Nigerians 6 months stay without a visa.
3. BENIN REPUBLIC – Capital Port Novo, a neighbouring country and a member of ECOWAS allows Nigerian citizens 90 days visa-free entry.
4. BURKINA FASO – Capital Ouagadougou, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
5. CAMBODIA – Capital – Phnom Penh, a southeastern Asia allows Nigerian citizens 30 days visa on arrival.
6. CAMEROON – Capital – Yaounde, a neighbouring country to the East, has visa abolition agreement with Nigeria and allows Nigerian citizens 90 days visa-free entry.
7. CAPE VERDE – Capital – Praia. An Island country in the Atlantic ocean, off the western coast of the African continent, near Senegal, allows Nigerians visa-free entry.
8. CHAD – Capital – N’Djamena, a neighbouring country to the north-east, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
9. COMOROS ISLAND – Capital – Moroni, situated in the Mozambique channels, close to Madagascar and Mozambique, enable Nigerian citizens visa on arrival.
10. IVORY COAST – Capital – Abidjan, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
11. DJIBOUTI – Capital – Djibouti, is a North African country, allows Nigerian citizens 31 days evisa on arrival
12. DOMINICA – Capital – Roseau is a Caribbean country. Located in North America, neighbouring Haiti allows Nigerian citizens 6 months of visa-free entry.
13. ETHIOPIA – Addis Ababa, the headquarters of the African Union enables Nigerian citizens to come in 90 days evisa on arrival, which is available only at Addis Ababa Bole international airport.
14. FIJI ISLANDS – Capital Suva, is a South Pacific nation, located in Oceania and Australia, allows Nigerians 4 months visa-free entry, with the possibility of extension of residence permits.
15. GABON – Capital – Libreville, a Central African country allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival obtainable at Libreville International airport.
16. THE GAMBIA – Capital – Banjul a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
17. GEORGIA – Capital – Tbilisi, is located at the intersection of Eastern Europe and Western Asia. Neighbouring Russian and Turkey allows Nigerians visa on arrival provided they have Schengen visa on arrival.
18. GHANA – Capital Accra, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
19. GUINEA – Capital Conakry, neighbouring Ghana, is an ECOWAS member, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
20. GUINEA BISSAU – Capital Bissau, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
21. HAITI – Capital – Port du Prince, a Caribbean country located in the continent of North America, allows Nigerian citizens 3 months visa-free entry.
22. IRAN – Capital – Tehran, an Islamic country located between Asia and the Middle East, allows Nigerian citizens Visa on arrival.
23. KENYA – Capital – Nairobi, an East African country allows Nigerians 3 months visa on arrival.
24. KYRGYZSTAN – Capital – Bishkek, a Central Asian country allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival, however, the holder must arrive via Manas International Airport.
25. LESOTHO – Capital – Maseru, a Southern African country allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival.
26. LIBERIA – Capital – Monrovia, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
27. MADAGASCAR – Capital Antananarivo, an island country located in the Indian Ocean, East of Mozambique, allows Nigerians 90 days visa on arrival.
28. MALDIVES – Capital Male, is a chain of 1192 islands, West of Sri Lanka, a commonwealth country, allows Nigerian citizens 30 days Visa On arrival.
29. MALI – Capital – Bamako, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
30. MAURITANIA – Capital – Nouakchott, a large sub-Sahara African country allows Nigerian citizens Visa on arrival.
31. MAURITIUS – Capital – Port Louis, is an island located in Eastern Africa, allows Nigerian citizens 2 weeks visa on arrival.
32. MICRONESIA – Capital – Weno, an Island country located in the Western Pacific ocean and it is a widely scattered island, allows Nigerian citizens 30 days visa-free entry.
33. MOZAMBIQUE – Capital – Maputo, a country located on the southeast coast of Africa, allows Nigerians 30 days Visa On arrival.
34. NAMIBIA – Capital – Windhoek, a Southern African country allows Nigerian citizens Visa on arrival.
35. NIGER REPUBLIC – Capital – Niamey, the Nigeria neighbour to the north-west, is an ECOWAS member allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
36. PAKISTAN – Capital – Islamabad, a large country located in South Asia allows Nigerian citizens online visa.
37. PALAU – Capital – Melekeok, is a group of Islands in the Micronesia area of Oceania south-east of Philippines, allows Nigerian citizens 30 days Free visa on arrival.
38. QATAR – Capital – Doha, a Middle East country located in the Persian Gulf allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival.
39. RWANDA – Capital – Kigali, a country located between East and Central Africa allows Nigerian citizens 30 days visa on arrival.
40. SAINT KITTS AND NEVIS – Capital – Basseterre, An Island country in the West Indies, allows Nigerian citizens 3 months visa-free entry.
41. SAMOA – Capital Apia, located in the continent of Oceania and Australia, allows Nigerians 60 days Free Entry permit on arrival.
42. SAO TOME AND PRINCIPE – Capital – Sao Tome, an Island country located on the Equator in the Gulf of Guinea, Central Africa, allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival.
43. SENEGAL – Capital – Dakar, is a West African country and a member of ECOWAS allows Nigerian citizens 90 days visa-free entry.
44. SEYCHELLES – Capital – Victoria, located in the Indian Ocean, North East of Madagascar, allows Nigerians visa on arrival, but approval must be obtained before you travelled.
45. SIERRA LEONE – Capital – Freetown, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry.
46. SOMALIA – Capital – Mogadishu, located in North East Africa, neighbouring Kenya an Ethiopia, allows Nigerian citizens 30 days Visa On arrival.
47. SOUTH SUDAN – Capital – Juba, a North-Eastern African country allows Nigerian citizens Electronic visa obtainable online and presentation at the time of travel.
48. SURINAME – Capital – Paramaribo, a Southern American country allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival.
49. TIMOR-LESTE – Capital – Dili, an island country located in the continent of Asia, allows Nigerians 30 days Visa On arrival.
50. TOGO – Capital Lome, a West African country and a member of ECOWAS, allows Nigerian citizens visa-free.
51. TUVALU – Capital – Funafuti, an Island country located in the continent of Oceania and Australia, enable Nigerians 30 days Visa On arrival.
52. UGANDA – Capital – Kampala, an East African country, allows Nigerian citizens Visa on arrival.
53. VANUATU – Capital – Port Vila, an Island country located in South Pacific Ocean east of Australia, allows Nigerian citizens 30 days visa-free entry.
54. ZAMBIA – Capital – Lusaka, an East African country allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival.
55. ZIMBABWE -Capital – Harare, a Southern African country allows Nigerian citizens evisa on arrival.
NIGERIA PASSPORT VISA FREE COUNTRIES IN EUROPE OR OTHER PART OF THE WORLD.
The following are partially recognised countries/territories that allows Nigerian citizens visa-free entry or visa on arrival.
1. PALESTINE: Visa-free entry.
2. COOK ISLANDS: 31 days visa-free entry.
3. NIUE: 30 days visa-free entry.
4. SOMALILAND: 30 days Visa on arrival.
5. MONTSERRAT: Visa-free entry.
6. PITCAIRN ISLANDS: 14 days visa-free entry.
7. SAINT HELENA: evisa on arrival.
8. SOUTH OSSETIA: Visa-free entry.
9. TRANSNISTRIA: visa-free entry.
10. ASCENSION ISLAND: 3 months evisa on arrival.
11. SAINT HELENA: evisa on arrival.
BASIC REQUIREMENTS
1. An International passport with at least six months validity.
2. Airline return ticket.
3. Nigeria port health card, popularly called ‘yellow card’.
4. Basic travelling allowance.
5. Hotel reservation.

